rComments: Boring and dry as all. Class is easy but mandatory attendance and absolutely braindead subject matter make it difficult to stay awake.

Dr. Sutherland was a fairly good professor. She was nice, spoke clearly and sounded passionate about cinema. Her powerpoints were minimal, with only quotes from the readings on them. She offered no way of reviewing what she taught later, so taking notes is a must. The papers are pretty simple. There's a lot of class time, about 6 hours/week.
She had minimal power points and was all over the place with her thought processes, pretty boring classes.
Very poor Overall experience for a course I find interesting.

She's a no BS Prof! Her class is also extremely hard. BUT, she is clearly very sharp. But what is most important is that she clearly cares about her students. I had class during her office hours and she made sure that she found time for me to see her around my schedule. If you get her as a Prof you are more than lucky!

Professor Sutherland is great.  She knows her stuff, challenges her students and makes thoughtful and interesting connections between philosophical theory and real world examples.  I'd highly recommend her.  However, you'll need to work for your grade in her class.  She's especially picky about writing!

Excellent prof. Challenging materials and difficult readings but worth digging into because the broader themes can be applied to other courses. Her class has changed the way I think about the world and how it operates.  The TA is useless, never said a word to us all year during screenings.
